# Adapters: interfaces and naming

**Contracts** live in `protocol/src/lib/protocol/interfaces/` (e.g. `database.interface.ts`, `storage.interface.ts`). **Implementations** live in `protocol/src/adapters/` and must not rename concepts after the library (Drizzle, Redis, S3, etc.).

## Pattern

`{concept}.adapter.ts` — **concept** is the protocol role. Tests: `{concept}.adapter.spec.ts`.

## Examples

| Use | Avoid |
|-----|--------|
| `database.adapter.ts` | `drizzle.adapter.ts` |
| `cache.adapter.ts` | `redis.adapter.ts` (for cache) |
| `queue.adapter.ts` | `bullmq.adapter.ts` |
| `storage.adapter.ts` | `s3.adapter.ts` |

Split cache vs queue when both exist; do not collapse unrelated roles into one file name.
